<DOC><DOCNO> AP880315-0087 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-15-88 1005EST</FILEID><FIRST>d a PM-BRF--BoxingInjury     03-15 0162</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Boxing Injury,0167</SECOND><HEAD>Marine Suffers Critical Injury During Championship Fight</HEAD><DATELINE>SAN DIEGO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A Marine amateur boxer was in critical butstable condition today after he was injured during the Armed ForcesBoxing Championships here, officials said.   Lance Cpl. Rickey Uzzel, 22, of Austin, Texas, was in theintensive care unit at San Diego Naval Hospital, hospital officialssaid this morning.   Uzzel was under sedation and was stable after receiving therapyto reduce pressure on his brain, said Lt. Pat Killy, hospitalspokeswoman.   Navy and other military officials were not available for commentMonday about the injury, a spokeswoman said.   The Marine was knocked out Thursday during thelight-middleweight championship match with James Crisp, an Armyboxer who last fall was ranked eighth by the USA Amateur BoxingFederation in the 156-pound class.   The injury occurred during 23 seconds into the second round of athree-round match.   Last year, boxing matches here among recruits were stopped afteran 18-year-old died.</TEXT></DOC>